Rating: 4
I don't know how such a simple recipe can be so extraordinary, but we absolutely loved this! We used a local organic pork loin. I forgot about marinating it with the rub in advance, so I stabbed it all over with a small knife to help the flavors penetrate and let it sit while I cut and chopped the veggies. Once it was cooked, I took the pork out and cut it up into stew chunks, then put it back and let it bake for another half hour or so. We couldn't get over how good it was. I'm going to try this recipe with chicken next--I think that would be wonderful, too.

