Rating: 4
I was going to add mushrooms as recommended in the reviews, but then I forgot. When the pork finished cooking, the peppers looked so limp and body-less that I thought they would be nasty to eat. So I pulled out the pork, boiled the sauce down by almost half, and used an immersion blender to puree the remainder. I cannot recommend this enough! The pork was spectacularly tender, and the sauce was superb. I served it all over buttered egg noodles, and my guests devoured it. Next time, I'll probably add the mushrooms, but I'm not sure if I'll puree them as well, or saute them separately and add them after pureeing during further reduction.

